    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="359"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Reidun/114: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 15, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Your April 8, 11 a.m. Treaty referred to is presumably liquor treaty signed
                    May 24, 1924. This treaty has no application to <hi rend="italic">Reidun</hi>
                    <pb facs="0524" n="444" xml:id="pg_444"/> case since vessel came voluntarily
                    into our jurisdiction and thereby the ship itself and those on board by their
                    own act became subject to our laws. The seizure of the vessel and the indictment
                    and arrest of the officers were normal result of their previous conduct. The
                    full protection of the law and recourse to our courts is open to them if they
                    wish to avail themselves thereof, and suit to recover vessel instituted at New
                    York.</p>
                <p>See instruction No. 43, March 31, 1936.<note n="61" xml:id="d359fn61">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
